Money Stuff =0A What if the US Securities and Exchange Commission never bri=
ngs another =0Aenforcement case=3F What if it=E2=80=99s like =E2=80=9Cahh, =
go ahead, do all the fraud =0A=0A=0A <> =0A =0A<https://sli.bloomberg.com/c=
lick=3Fs=3D825881&stpe=3Ddefault&li=3D12371556&m=3D21d6dea82d6b16615cf44233=
be620525&p=3D01212025>=0A=0A=0A=0ASEC: General=0A=0AWhat if the US Securiti=
es and Exchange Commission never brings another =0Aenforcement case=3F What=
 if it=E2=80=99s like =E2=80=9Cahh, go ahead, do all the fraud you want=E2=
=80=9D=3F =0AWhat if the only enforcement cases are against BlackRock fordo=
ing ESG investing =0A<>, or against short sellers <> of Trump Media & Techn=
ology Group Corp.=3F Crime =0Amight be legal now, if you are a vocal enough=
 supporter of Donald Trump, and =0Athe financial and crypto industries are =
rushing to support him. It=E2=80=99s hard to =0Aimagine anyone getting in t=
rouble fortexting about work from their personal =0Aphones <>, now.=0A=0AJu=
st in case, the SEC filed a ton of enforcement actions on Friday, the last =
